1
00:01:49,849 --> 00:01:54,688
{\an8}[GAMILIAN RECON
speaking Gamilan]

2
00:01:58,191 --> 00:02:00,360
[KOBASHI] So we're
restricted to visual range?

3
00:02:00,443 --> 00:02:02,278
Talk about old school!

4
00:02:07,117 --> 00:02:08,368
[KOBASHI]
Captain!

5
00:02:08,451 --> 00:02:10,453
[KATO] Yeah, I see 'em.
Time to greet our guests.

6
00:02:10,537 --> 00:02:12,330
Don't let them kill you.
You kill them!

7
00:02:12,414 --> 00:02:13,665
[FALCON PILOTS]
Yes, sir!

8
00:02:20,672 --> 00:02:24,217
{\an8}[SNUKA PILOT speaking Gamilan]

9
00:02:26,177 --> 00:02:28,972
[BRIDGE OFFICER A] Attack Force
Group Two, launch immediately.

10
00:02:29,055 --> 00:02:32,392
Repeat: Attack Force Group Two,
launch immediately.

11
00:02:51,119 --> 00:02:53,496
[BERGER]
Fomt Berger, launching.

12
00:03:09,596 --> 00:03:11,806
[BRIDGE OFFICER A] Attack Force
Group Two is in position.

13
00:03:11,890 --> 00:03:14,017
Activating Matter
Transfer System!

14
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:19,314
Inputting recon data now, sir.
Coordinates: Over their ship.

15
00:03:19,397 --> 00:03:22,692
Matter Transfer Waves
calibrated and ready.

16
00:03:22,776 --> 00:03:24,110
Then fire!

17
00:03:44,297 --> 00:03:46,633
[BERGER]
There they are.

18
00:03:46,716 --> 00:03:48,968
[gasps] They're
right over us, sir!

19
00:03:49,052 --> 00:03:50,053
[OKITA]
Huh?

20
00:04:08,822 --> 00:04:10,365
[NAV. OFFICER A]
Direct hit!

21
00:04:12,701 --> 00:04:14,119
--[SHIMA] Damage control!
--[OTA] Torpedoes coming fast!

22
00:04:14,202 --> 00:04:16,204
Gunners, AA formation!

23
00:04:21,292 --> 00:04:23,253
Maintain a wall of fire!

24
00:04:25,130 --> 00:04:27,298
Secondary Gunport One is hit!

25
00:04:27,382 --> 00:04:28,466
Damn it!

26
00:04:28,550 --> 00:04:31,678
[YAMAMOTO]
Yamamoto to Bridge.

27
00:04:31,761 --> 00:04:33,972
Alpha Two launching now.

28
00:04:39,978 --> 00:04:42,147
[BERGER]
Melhi, you target the catapult.

29
00:04:42,230 --> 00:04:44,190
I'll knock out their eyes.

30
00:04:51,865 --> 00:04:53,450
[BERGER]
We don't want to sink it. Yet.

31
00:04:53,533 --> 00:04:54,284
[CO-PILOT A]
Enemy behind us!

32
00:04:54,367 --> 00:04:55,744
[BERGER]
Huh?

33
00:04:55,827 --> 00:04:57,662
I won't let you get
away with this!

34
00:04:57,746 --> 00:04:59,080
[OTA] Port-side catapult
has been destroyed!

35
00:04:59,164 --> 00:04:59,998
[SAIJO]
Radar, system hit!

36
00:05:00,081 --> 00:05:01,541
[KODAI]
Gunners, keep firing!

37
00:05:01,624 --> 00:05:03,918
[AIHARA] <i>Yamato</i> to all
fighters! Do you copy?

38
00:05:04,002 --> 00:05:06,046
This is the <i>Yamato</i>
with a change of orders.

39
00:05:06,129 --> 00:05:07,589
We are under surprise attack!

40
00:05:07,672 --> 00:05:10,258
All fighters are to return
immediately to close perimeter

41
00:05:10,342 --> 00:05:11,426
and defend the <i>Yamato</i> !

42
00:05:11,509 --> 00:05:14,220
[KATO]
What? We're chasing decoys?

43
00:05:14,304 --> 00:05:15,847
[KOBASHI]
Captain, what do we do?

44
00:05:15,930 --> 00:05:18,767
[PILOT screams]

45
00:05:18,850 --> 00:05:20,810
[DAIKUHARA] Don't lose
your nerve, Kobashi.

46
00:05:20,894 --> 00:05:23,063
I'll shoot down
anyone on your tail!

47
00:05:29,611 --> 00:05:30,945
[KOBASHI]
Daikuhara's down!

48
00:05:31,029 --> 00:05:32,906
[gasps]

49
00:05:32,989 --> 00:05:35,075
[KATO]
Akira, keep 'em busy!

50
00:05:51,132 --> 00:05:52,384
[CO-PILOT A]
That was one Fighter?

51
00:05:52,467 --> 00:05:55,345
[BERGER] Doesn't matter.
Our job's done. Withdraw.

52
00:05:59,516 --> 00:06:01,643
Their fighter
group's retreating.

53
00:06:01,726 --> 00:06:03,103
[ENOMOTO]
Bridge Three to Bridge One.

54
00:06:03,186 --> 00:06:04,229
Our converter's shot.

55
00:06:04,312 --> 00:06:06,731
We cannot deploy
Wave Motion Shields.

56
00:06:06,815 --> 00:06:08,149
If we don't patch this,

57
00:06:08,233 --> 00:06:10,652
it's going to affect
inertial control.

58
00:06:10,735 --> 00:06:12,570
I'll go supervise repairs.

59
00:06:12,654 --> 00:06:14,364
But those fighters came
down out of nowhere.

60
00:06:14,447 --> 00:06:15,740
How'd they do that?

61
00:06:15,824 --> 00:06:17,659
[OKITA]
They warped.

62
00:06:17,742 --> 00:06:18,993
There's no way.

63
00:06:19,077 --> 00:06:21,371
Those small fighters could
never hold a warp drive.

64
00:06:21,454 --> 00:06:24,791
You can't win if you only rely
on what you think you know.

65
00:06:24,874 --> 00:06:27,585
They've got one hell
of a commander.

66
00:06:30,463 --> 00:06:33,466
Excellent bit of flying, Berger.

67
00:06:33,550 --> 00:06:36,052
Surface the ship and
release our guests.

68
00:06:41,016 --> 00:06:43,643
[BELLGER]
Remember that face, soldiers.

69
00:06:43,727 --> 00:06:45,854
I gotta say, she's beautiful.

70
00:06:45,937 --> 00:06:47,689
Well, that's nobility for you.

71
00:06:47,772 --> 00:06:48,648
[RAITSCH]
Hm.

72
00:06:48,732 --> 00:06:50,358
Don't fall in love, Norran.

73
00:06:50,442 --> 00:06:51,901
[ORTSCHETT grunts]

74
00:06:51,985 --> 00:06:53,194
[ORTSCHETT]
I'm not!

75
00:07:34,527 --> 00:07:35,695
[AIHARA]
All damage teams,

76
00:07:35,779 --> 00:07:37,989
full priority to Bridge
Three converter...

77
00:07:38,073 --> 00:07:40,283
Norran, stay here and
keep that airlock secure

78
00:07:40,367 --> 00:07:41,659
until we get back.

79
00:07:41,743 --> 00:07:43,203
Zar Belk.

80
00:07:45,830 --> 00:07:47,082
[HEYDELN]
So tell me, Barlen.

81
00:07:47,165 --> 00:07:49,751
How does it feel sittin'
in the pilot seat again?

82
00:07:49,834 --> 00:07:51,044
[BARLEN]
Feels wonderful.

83
00:07:51,127 --> 00:07:53,672
I may be all scars and
wrinkles on the outside,

84
00:07:53,755 --> 00:07:56,132
but I'm still as sharp
as the day I enlisted.

85
00:07:56,216 --> 00:07:59,135
[HEYDELN laughs]

86
00:07:59,219 --> 00:08:01,346
<i>Garlent</i> primed and launching.

87
00:08:13,983 --> 00:08:15,485
[OKITA]
That was only the start.

88
00:08:15,568 --> 00:08:17,862
Their commander will
have more surprises.

89
00:08:17,946 --> 00:08:20,365
Everyone stay on the
lookout for the next one.

90
00:08:20,448 --> 00:08:23,076
How can we, sir?
Our sensors are down.

91
00:08:23,159 --> 00:08:25,286
With the <i>Yamato</i> flying
blind and deaf now,

92
00:08:25,370 --> 00:08:27,747
our human senses are
all we can rely on.

93
00:08:27,831 --> 00:08:30,583
That and our wits.

94
00:08:30,667 --> 00:08:34,462
There should be a current
of ion turbulence nearby.

95
00:08:34,546 --> 00:08:37,048
Use the data we've already
gathered to find it.

96
00:08:37,132 --> 00:08:38,299
[OTA, KIRYU]
Yes, sir.

97
00:08:40,677 --> 00:08:42,387
Hostile! Dead ahead!

98
00:08:45,348 --> 00:08:46,808
[BARLEN]
Here's your gift, Terons!

99
00:08:46,891 --> 00:08:48,476
Hope you like it!

100
00:09:02,699 --> 00:09:04,117
[KODAI]
A dud?

101
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:06,327
[BARLEN]
The present has been delivered.

102
00:09:06,411 --> 00:09:08,747
We're on our way back--

103
00:09:08,830 --> 00:09:10,331
You're finished!

104
00:09:16,963 --> 00:09:18,673
[ALL yell]

105
00:09:26,765 --> 00:09:28,725
[IWATA]
Okay! To the windows!

106
00:09:28,808 --> 00:09:29,309
[TACTICAL OFFICERS]
Right!

107
00:09:29,392 --> 00:09:30,769
Yurisha!

108
00:09:30,852 --> 00:09:31,811
[YURISHA]
Hoshina.

109
00:09:31,895 --> 00:09:32,937
They could come from
any direction...

110
00:09:33,021 --> 00:09:35,774
It's dangerous here.
They could attack.

111
00:09:35,857 --> 00:09:37,067
[TACTICAL OFFICERS]
Yes, sir!

112
00:09:38,568 --> 00:09:40,153
Be careful.

113
00:09:40,236 --> 00:09:42,447
What is that? A bomb?

114
00:09:42,530 --> 00:09:44,741
[KIRYU] Sending report
on dud to Bridge Three.

115
00:09:44,824 --> 00:09:47,619
[NANBU] Wave Motion Gun
Control Room, report.

116
00:10:02,425 --> 00:10:05,637
Captain! It's moving
towards the gun's chamber!

117
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:07,222
[WAVE GUN CM A]
Chamber pressure dropping!

118
00:10:07,305 --> 00:10:09,724
[WAVE GUN CM B]
Close the safety valves, now!

119
00:10:11,267 --> 00:10:13,311
[WAVE GUN CM C]
Watch out! Hurry!

120
00:10:22,278 --> 00:10:24,239
[BRIDGE 3 OFFICER A]
Inertial control is down.

121
00:10:24,322 --> 00:10:26,658
[ENOMOTO] I guess it
wasn't a dud, after all.

122
00:10:26,741 --> 00:10:28,952
[SANADA]
Most likely a delay fuse.

123
00:10:29,035 --> 00:10:30,453
[ENOMOTO]
This is bad.

124
00:10:31,788 --> 00:10:34,040
[SANADA]
This is Sanada, on Bridge Three.

125
00:10:34,124 --> 00:10:35,208
Go ahead.

126
00:10:35,291 --> 00:10:37,085
I have a suggestion.

127
00:10:43,675 --> 00:10:45,301
[AIHARA] All available
crewmembers not assigned

128
00:10:45,385 --> 00:10:47,554
to damage teams or
active battle stations

129
00:10:47,637 --> 00:10:49,597
are needed for
emergency watch duty.

130
00:10:49,681 --> 00:10:51,224
Position yourselves at
stations with exterior...

131
00:10:51,307 --> 00:10:52,892
[HOSHINA]
Hey. Hold up.

132
00:10:54,019 --> 00:10:56,771
Don't think we've met before.
Where're you stationed?

133
00:10:56,855 --> 00:10:59,524
[BELLGER]
Oh, uh. Me?

134
00:10:59,607 --> 00:11:00,650
[gasps]

135
00:11:00,734 --> 00:11:02,444
[KIRYU]
Gunfire on Deck Six!

136
00:11:02,527 --> 00:11:04,946
Sound print matches
Gamilan weapon, sir!

137
00:11:05,030 --> 00:11:06,990
Send security to investigate.

138
00:11:07,073 --> 00:11:08,658
Kodai, take command.

139
00:11:08,742 --> 00:11:09,826
Yes, sir!

140
00:11:20,211 --> 00:11:21,921
[YURISHA]
Hoshina!

141
00:11:22,005 --> 00:11:25,091
No!

142
00:11:29,304 --> 00:11:31,264
They've seen our faces.

143
00:11:31,348 --> 00:11:32,974
[MORI]
Hey, what's going on here?

144
00:11:35,810 --> 00:11:38,396
It's the Iscandarian.

145
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:39,939
[RAITSCH]
Sorry about this.

146
00:11:43,276 --> 00:11:44,444
[RAITSCH]
Got her.

147
00:12:01,878 --> 00:12:03,380
[ANALYZER]
I am surprised that this weapon

148
00:12:03,463 --> 00:12:05,465
could be infiltrated so easily.

149
00:12:05,548 --> 00:12:08,009
[NIIMI] Probably because it
wasn't built as a weapon.

150
00:12:08,093 --> 00:12:10,011
I think they converted
existing tech

151
00:12:10,095 --> 00:12:11,721
that wasn't designed
for warfare.

152
00:12:11,805 --> 00:12:13,973
[ANALYZER]
A logical conclusion.

153
00:12:14,057 --> 00:12:16,685
Seems the enemy's
starting to get desperate.

154
00:12:16,768 --> 00:12:18,395
[chuckles]

155
00:12:18,478 --> 00:12:20,230
But then, so are we.

156
00:12:25,026 --> 00:12:26,111
[yells]

157
00:12:26,194 --> 00:12:28,321
Stop it! Get off me!

158
00:12:31,741 --> 00:12:33,868
[SAWAMURA]
You okay, rookie?

159
00:12:33,952 --> 00:12:34,869
Sawamura?

160
00:12:34,953 --> 00:12:36,621
[SAWAMURA]
Don't push yourself.

161
00:12:39,416 --> 00:12:41,376
[SAWAMURA]
Enemy ship, ten o'clock!

162
00:12:43,503 --> 00:12:45,088
[KOBASHI]
That's a carrier.

163
00:12:46,464 --> 00:12:47,590
[SAWAMURA]
Kobashi, wait!

164
00:12:47,674 --> 00:12:48,550
[KOBASHI]
I've got this!

165
00:12:48,633 --> 00:12:50,885
[SAWAMURA]
Kobashi! Abort!

166
00:12:50,969 --> 00:12:53,388
I'm no coward,
and I'm gonna prove it!

167
00:12:55,265 --> 00:12:56,683
[BRIDGE OFFICER C]
Enemy approaching portside!

168
00:12:56,766 --> 00:12:58,977
Fire anti-air weapons!

169
00:13:04,816 --> 00:13:06,192
Mother!

170
00:13:09,195 --> 00:13:10,739
Kobashi!

171
00:13:18,163 --> 00:13:19,539
Damn it!

172
00:13:46,316 --> 00:13:47,609
[KATO]
Not bad.

173
00:13:51,363 --> 00:13:54,824
{\an8}[GETTO speaking Gamilan]

174
00:13:54,908 --> 00:13:57,410
{\an8}[SNUKA PILOT B speaking Gamilan]

175
00:13:57,494 --> 00:13:58,828
{\an8}[GETTO speaking Gamilan]

176
00:14:01,790 --> 00:14:03,416
{\an8}[GETTO speaking Gamilan]

177
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:04,959
[KATO]
You're mine!

178
00:14:07,379 --> 00:14:09,547
{\an8}[GETTO speaking Gamilan]

179
00:14:23,019 --> 00:14:24,312
I can help.

180
00:14:27,190 --> 00:14:29,025
[KODAI]
Gamilan soldiers?

181
00:14:29,109 --> 00:14:29,651
[KODAI gasps]

182
00:14:29,734 --> 00:14:30,735
Mori!

183
00:14:33,405 --> 00:14:34,572
Get her to the ship!

184
00:14:34,656 --> 00:14:36,658
[ORTSCHETT]
Yes, sir!

185
00:14:36,741 --> 00:14:38,952
[SECURITY C] Security to Bridge,
Gamilans are onboard!

186
00:14:39,035 --> 00:14:40,286
Captain!

187
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,668
Uh! No!

188
00:14:46,751 --> 00:14:48,795
Captain Gelt!

189
00:14:48,878 --> 00:14:51,548
Go, Norran. Escape!

190
00:14:51,631 --> 00:14:54,384
Fulfill our mission,
and make Zaltz proud!

191
00:15:01,099 --> 00:15:03,226
Long live, Zaltz!

192
00:15:06,396 --> 00:15:07,605
Yuki!

193
00:15:09,190 --> 00:15:11,359
No, Yuki! Yuki!

194
00:15:14,154 --> 00:15:19,075
[FLAKEN] Surface. Let's pick
up our little suckerfish.

195
00:15:37,302 --> 00:15:39,888
What do I do? What do I do?

196
00:15:43,767 --> 00:15:45,352
[KODAI]
Yuki!

197
00:15:47,729 --> 00:15:49,522
[BRIDGE OFFICER A] Encrypted
message from the <i>Hound</i> .

198
00:15:49,606 --> 00:15:51,775
The suckerfish has our target.

199
00:15:53,401 --> 00:15:56,237
Schderg requesting permission
to launch the attack teams.

200
00:15:56,321 --> 00:15:57,781
Shall we, sir?

201
00:15:57,864 --> 00:15:59,032
[DOMEL]
When that drill explodes,

202
00:15:59,115 --> 00:16:01,159
the <i>Yamato</i> should
be ripped apart.

203
00:16:01,242 --> 00:16:03,161
But there are no
certainties in battle.

204
00:16:03,244 --> 00:16:04,245
We'll send out the bombers

205
00:16:04,329 --> 00:16:07,248
in case they need
to finish the job.

206
00:16:07,332 --> 00:16:10,335
Attack Force Group Three.
Launch when ready!

207
00:16:32,691 --> 00:16:37,112
[NIIMI] Niimi to Bridge. The
detonator has been disabled.

208
00:16:37,195 --> 00:16:40,782
Well done. You may
have saved the ship.

209
00:16:41,908 --> 00:16:43,368
[ANALYZER]
Good job.

210
00:17:12,647 --> 00:17:14,357
Die, Gamilans!

211
00:17:19,821 --> 00:17:22,365
[SCIENCE DIV. OFFICERS scream]

212
00:17:32,417 --> 00:17:35,754
[KATO] Damn it.
You'll all pay for this!

213
00:17:39,174 --> 00:17:42,677
[KRAITZE] Attack Force Group
Three requesting reinforcements!

214
00:17:42,761 --> 00:17:46,389
Enemy fighters have engaged,
they're coming down strong!

215
00:17:46,473 --> 00:17:47,891
You're dead!

216
00:17:54,439 --> 00:17:56,066
General?

217
00:17:56,149 --> 00:17:59,903
Evidently the gods want me
to finish the <i>Yamato</i> myself.

218
00:18:01,112 --> 00:18:03,656
Then I shall do their bidding.

219
00:18:03,740 --> 00:18:05,658
Order fleet to strike!

220
00:18:14,542 --> 00:18:16,586
Mooring Cosmo Zero!

221
00:18:16,670 --> 00:18:18,880
[SAIJO]
The fighters have returned, sir.

222
00:18:18,963 --> 00:18:22,217
Twelve were lost.

223
00:18:22,300 --> 00:18:24,219
Get them ready for re-launch.

224
00:18:24,302 --> 00:18:27,639
Ota, did you find
that ion current?

225
00:18:27,722 --> 00:18:29,140
[OTA]
Yes, sir.

226
00:18:29,224 --> 00:18:32,977
[IWATA] Watch Team to Bridge.
Enemy ships to starboard!

227
00:18:36,356 --> 00:18:38,274
[OKITA]
So they've come.

228
00:18:46,658 --> 00:18:47,659
[NIIMI]
Analyzer!

229
00:18:47,742 --> 00:18:49,202
[ANALYZER]
Go on.

230
00:19:09,014 --> 00:19:13,018
Turn the ship! Forty
to port! Combat Speed!

231
00:19:13,101 --> 00:19:15,770
But, sir! That'll take
us to the ion current!

232
00:19:15,854 --> 00:19:18,106
If the storm sucks us in,
we'll be helpless!

233
00:19:18,189 --> 00:19:19,649
That's an order, Lieutenant!

234
00:19:19,733 --> 00:19:21,067
Uh. Right!

235
00:19:21,151 --> 00:19:23,486
Changing course
40 degrees to port.

236
00:19:27,073 --> 00:19:29,200
[OKITA] Ota, send that
drill's flight path

237
00:19:29,284 --> 00:19:30,660
to the weapons officer.

238
00:19:30,744 --> 00:19:32,203
[OTA]
Aye-aye!

239
00:19:32,287 --> 00:19:33,997
[OKITA] Nanbu, when its axis
lines up with the enemy fleet,

240
00:19:34,080 --> 00:19:35,373
light it up.

241
00:19:35,457 --> 00:19:36,374
Sir!

242
00:19:36,458 --> 00:19:38,585
It's a tough shot,
sir. Don't miss!

243
00:19:38,668 --> 00:19:41,755
Don't you worry.
Guns are my specialty.

244
00:19:48,053 --> 00:19:49,387
[BARECK]
Evade!

245
00:20:02,108 --> 00:20:03,109
[LAMBEA CM A]
The <i>Schderg</i> is down!

246
00:20:03,193 --> 00:20:04,110
Just stay calm!

247
00:20:04,194 --> 00:20:05,403
[LAMBEA OFFICER A]
Enemy is firing!

248
00:20:05,487 --> 00:20:07,155
[BERGER]
Send me out there! Now!

249
00:20:07,238 --> 00:20:08,531
Don't be a fool!

250
00:20:08,615 --> 00:20:10,200
I want revenge!

251
00:20:14,079 --> 00:20:16,956
Damn it! It can't
end this way!

252
00:20:27,008 --> 00:20:27,967
[HEYDELN]
Berger!

253
00:20:28,051 --> 00:20:30,011
All cannons fire!

254
00:20:34,808 --> 00:20:36,101
Fire!

255
00:20:44,484 --> 00:20:45,902
[BRIDGE OFFICER A]
Direct hit!

256
00:20:45,985 --> 00:20:47,529
Keep calm, and fire!

257
00:20:47,612 --> 00:20:50,490
Concentrate everything
we've got left on that ship!

258
00:20:57,080 --> 00:21:00,667
I told you, keep
firing! Now what?

259
00:21:03,044 --> 00:21:04,671
Right the ship, now!

260
00:21:04,754 --> 00:21:05,797
[BRIDGE OFFICER A]
We can't, sir!

261
00:21:05,880 --> 00:21:07,340
We're caught in the ion current!

262
00:21:07,424 --> 00:21:09,050
That was their plan?

263
00:21:14,514 --> 00:21:17,183
The ion storm current
has caught them, sir!

264
00:21:18,476 --> 00:21:20,020
[DOMEL]
Of course.

265
00:21:20,103 --> 00:21:22,522
They lured me into this trap.

266
00:21:25,817 --> 00:21:27,485
I let my arrogance consume me

267
00:21:27,569 --> 00:21:30,196
and tried to destroy
the <i>Yamato</i> myself.

268
00:21:30,280 --> 00:21:31,781
It's my fault.

269
00:21:31,865 --> 00:21:34,409
In the final hour,
I made a fatal mistake.

270
00:21:34,492 --> 00:21:35,910
[BRIDGE OFFICER B]
Engine output dropping!

271
00:21:35,994 --> 00:21:37,162
[HEYDELN]
Turn to port!

272
00:21:37,245 --> 00:21:38,079
[BRIDGE OFFICER B]
The helm's not responding!

273
00:21:38,163 --> 00:21:40,373
We've lost control of the ship!

274
00:21:40,457 --> 00:21:45,295
[DOMEL]
Elk Domel, ID-17492-Zeku.

275
00:21:45,378 --> 00:21:46,963
[HEYDELN]
General, don't.

276
00:21:47,047 --> 00:21:50,216
This is now a battle
between them and me.

277
00:21:50,300 --> 00:21:52,469
All crew abandon ship!

278
00:21:56,556 --> 00:21:57,807
[chuckles]

279
00:21:57,891 --> 00:21:59,225
Looks like we're all going
to be court-martialed

280
00:21:59,309 --> 00:22:01,728
for disobeying orders, sir.

281
00:22:16,117 --> 00:22:18,161
[HEYDELN]
Prepare to fire anchors!

282
00:22:26,670 --> 00:22:29,089
It sounds like we
have a new problem.

283
00:22:29,172 --> 00:22:30,715
I'm almost finished.

284
00:22:30,799 --> 00:22:32,759
[KIRYU] An enemy vessel
has latched onto us.

285
00:22:32,842 --> 00:22:34,135
[beeping]

286
00:22:34,219 --> 00:22:36,805
The enemy ship
is hailing us, sir.

287
00:22:36,888 --> 00:22:37,931
Video transmission.

288
00:22:38,014 --> 00:22:39,391
On screen.

289
00:22:45,397 --> 00:22:47,732
Let me speak to your captain.

290
00:22:47,816 --> 00:22:51,403
You're speaking to the captain
right now. Juzo Okita.

291
00:22:51,486 --> 00:22:52,737
Greetings.

292
00:22:52,821 --> 00:22:54,864
I'm Commander of the Milky
Way Galactic Theater,

293
00:22:54,948 --> 00:22:56,408
Elk Domel.

294
00:22:57,909 --> 00:23:00,120
I've been looking
forward to this moment.

295
00:23:00,203 --> 00:23:03,456
Glad to hear it.
Because I feel the same way.

296
00:23:03,540 --> 00:23:07,127
Captain Okita, allow me
to express my admiration

297
00:23:07,210 --> 00:23:09,129
for your exemplary command.

298
00:23:09,212 --> 00:23:12,382
Commander Domel,
this battle is over.

299
00:23:12,465 --> 00:23:15,677
I'd like to avoid more
bloodshed if we can.

300
00:23:15,760 --> 00:23:19,097
Let us pass, and we will
not fire on your ship.

301
00:23:20,849 --> 00:23:23,018
I can't do that.

302
00:23:23,101 --> 00:23:25,937
As a fellow leader,
I'd think you'd understand.

303
00:23:26,021 --> 00:23:28,189
If I allow the
<i>Yamato</i> safe passage,

304
00:23:28,273 --> 00:23:30,316
then all my men who have
given their lives today

305
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:32,652
will have done so in vain.

306
00:23:32,736 --> 00:23:37,657
Captain Okita, as a soldier--
no, more than that--as a man,

307
00:23:37,741 --> 00:23:39,743
I'm proud to have faced
an opponent like you

308
00:23:39,826 --> 00:23:41,077
before my death.

309
00:23:41,161 --> 00:23:42,996
It was a true honor.

310
00:23:44,205 --> 00:23:46,958
Bless the Terons,
and Gamilans alike,

311
00:23:47,042 --> 00:23:49,961
as we die in this battle.

312
00:23:50,045 --> 00:23:52,005
The enemy's going
to self-destruct.

313
00:23:52,088 --> 00:23:55,008
All crew on the lower
decks evacuate!

314
00:24:08,229 --> 00:24:09,731
Oh, Elk.

315
00:24:24,371 --> 00:24:26,164
Did we really make it?

